ğŸ”¶Persistent Volume (PV)
A Persistent Volume is a resource(piece of storage) in the cluster just like a node is a cluster resource. PVs are volume plugin that have a lifecycle â™»  independent of any individual Pod that uses the PV.

ğŸ”¶PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)
A PersistentVolumeClaim is a request for and claim to a PersistentVolume resource. Its similar to a Pod. Pods consume node resources and PVCs consume PV resources. Pods can request specific levels of resources i.e. CPUğŸ’», Memory, etc. Claim objects request a specific size, access mode, and StorageClass for the PersistentVolume. If a PersistentVolume that satisfies the request exists or can be provisioned, the PersistentVolumeClaim is bound ğŸ¤  to that PersistentVolume. 

Persistent Volumes support following Access Modes:

ğŸ”¸ReadWriteOnce: The volume can be mounted as read-write by a single pod (RWO).
ğŸ”¸ReadOnlyMany: The volume can be mounted read-only by many nodes (ROX).
ğŸ”¸ReadWriteMany: The volume can be mounted as read-write by many nodes (RWX).

SummaryğŸ—’of the process:

ğŸ”¹Create a PersistentVolume
ğŸ”¹Create a PersistentVolumeClaim
ğŸ”¹Create a Pod that uses the above created PersistentVolumeClaim for storage.
